</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">John Lindley (cinematographer)</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><span class="fn">John Lindley, <a href="/wiki/A.S.C." title="A.S.C." class="mw-redirect">A.S.C.</a></span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Born</th>
<td><span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1951-11-17</span>)</span> November 17, 1951 <span class="noprint ForceAgeToShow">(age&#160;63)</span><br />
<span class="birthplace"><a href="/wiki/New_York_City,_New_York" title="New York City, New York" class="mw-redirect">New York City, New York</a>, U.S.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Occupation</th>
<td class="role"><a href="/wiki/Cinematographer" title="Cinematographer">Cinematographer</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>John Warwick Lindley</b> (November 17, 1951 in <a href="/wiki/New_York_City" title="New York City">New York City</a>) is an American cinematographer best known for his work on such films as <i><a href="/wiki/Field_of_Dreams" title="Field of Dreams">Field of Dreams</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Bewitched_(2005_film)" title="Bewitched (2005 film)">Bewitched</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Pleasantville_(film)" title="Pleasantville (film)">Pleasantville</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/You%27ve_Got_Mail" title="You've Got Mail">You've Got Mail</a></i>.</p>
<p></p>
